Member Enumeration Documentation

enum ExpandedRouteItem::routeturn_t
 

The possible turns in a route.

Enumeration values:
UNDEFINED  Undefined turndescription.

Only for error-handling.

NO_TURN  Not really a turn.
START  Start, beginning of route.
START_WITH_U_TURN  Start by turning the car around.
FINALLY  Finally, end of route.
LEFT  Turn to the left.
AHEAD  Drive straight ahead.
RIGHT  Turn to the right.
U_TURN  U-turn.
FOLLOW_ROAD  Follow the same road.
ENTER_ROUNDABOUT  Drive into a roundabout.
EXIT_ROUNDABOUT  Drive out from a roundabout.
AHEAD_ROUNDABOUT  Drive ahead at the roundabout.
RIGHT_ROUNDABOUT  Drive right at the roundabout.
LEFT_ROUNDABOUT  Drive left at the roundabout.
U_TURN_ROUNDABOUT  Make a u-turn at the roundabout, ei.

exit in the same direction as you came.

ON_RAMP  Enter the highway by ramp.
OFF_RAMP_LEFT  Exit the highway by ramp.
OFF_RAMP_RIGHT  Exit the highway by ramp.
OFF_RAMP  Exit the highway by ramp.
ENTER_BUS  Enter bus.
EXIT_BUS  Exit bus.
CHANGE_BUS  Change to another bus.
KEEP_RIGHT  Hold to the right.

Choose the right road.

KEEP_LEFT  Hold to the left.

Choose the left road.

ENTER_FERRY  Drive onto a ferry.
EXIT_FERRY  Leave a ferry.
CHANGE_FERRY  Leave one ferry and enter an other one.
PARK_AND_WALK  Park vehicle here and walk on.
STATE_CHANGE  No true turndescription.

This is a waypoint indicating a state change

OFF_MAIN  Exit non highway road by ramp.
ON_MAIN  Enter non highway road by ramp.
